WEBVTT

00:01.139 --> 00:03.175
Previously onBarkskins...

00:03.244 --> 00:05.522
YVON: The Iroquois
always collect their dead.
What will you do

00:05.591 --> 00:07.938
when they come back
to make their own dead?

00:08.008 --> 00:10.217
It was a business dispute.

00:10.286 --> 00:14.221
I'm done with both you
and that English bastard Cooke.

00:14.911 --> 00:16.671
[screaming]

00:16.740 --> 00:18.018
[grunts]

00:18.087 --> 00:19.122
HAMISH:
Gus Lafarge is dead.

00:19.191 --> 00:22.022
I saw his end myself.

00:22.091 --> 00:23.782
COOKE:
The Company
did not send you here.

00:23.851 --> 00:25.922
If they had, you would know
that what happened...

00:25.991 --> 00:27.682
[yelling]

00:27.751 --> 00:28.787
Cross' idea.

00:28.856 --> 00:30.582
Cross is married to my sister.

00:30.651 --> 00:32.549
MELISSANDE:
The one on the end
is quite taken with you.

00:32.618 --> 00:35.069
He has a kind face
and not so old, I guess.

00:35.138 --> 00:37.175
MELISSANDE:
You need a good wife

00:37.244 --> 00:39.970
befitting a man
with your vision.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.455
COOKE:
I have another job for you.

00:41.524 --> 00:43.802
Take the boy into the woods.
He must

00:43.871 --> 00:45.045
not return.

00:53.950 --> 00:56.125
♪ ♪

01:26.016 --> 01:28.191
♪ ♪

01:45.484 --> 01:48.522
COOKE: ♪ My eyes shall then♪

01:48.591 --> 01:51.318
♪ Behold Thee♪

01:51.387 --> 01:54.424
♪ Upon Thy cross♪

01:54.493 --> 01:57.255
♪ Thy dwell♪

01:57.324 --> 01:59.878
♪ My heart in faith♪

01:59.947 --> 02:03.226
♪ Enfold Thee♪

02:03.295 --> 02:05.297
♪ Who dieth♪

02:05.366 --> 02:08.507
♪ Thus dies well.♪

02:24.627 --> 02:26.387
God is watching.

02:26.456 --> 02:30.046
He, uh, even watches us here

02:30.115 --> 02:31.875
in this speck of a town.

02:31.944 --> 02:33.705
Then he can see
what you have done.

02:33.774 --> 02:35.707
What is it that I have done
apart from putting food

02:35.776 --> 02:37.709
-on your family's table?
-God knows.

02:37.778 --> 02:39.538
Just as you know what happened
to my husband.

02:39.607 --> 02:41.920
God knows that Gus was

02:41.989 --> 02:43.680
a good and loyal man.

02:43.749 --> 02:44.992
Where is my son?

02:45.061 --> 02:47.891
He ran into the woods,
from what I was told.

02:48.996 --> 02:51.309
No. He would have been home
by now.

02:51.378 --> 02:54.104
I will find him.

02:54.174 --> 02:55.934
Now...

02:56.003 --> 02:58.868
we must see him into the earth
so that he may pass over.

02:58.937 --> 03:00.180
How will you find Thom?

03:03.942 --> 03:05.185
Charles,

03:05.254 --> 03:07.083
my new man,
will find him for you.

03:07.152 --> 03:09.672
I'm sorry for your loss.

03:11.501 --> 03:13.917
Did you know my husband?

03:13.986 --> 03:17.749
No, uh, but he was a good man,
I'm told.

03:17.818 --> 03:19.958
A steadfast man.

03:20.027 --> 03:21.822
My husband left me with nothing.

03:21.891 --> 03:23.479
Murdered.

03:23.548 --> 03:26.309
And now my son is lost
in the woods.

03:26.378 --> 03:27.966
I am widowed,

03:28.035 --> 03:30.727
and all of my days
will now be doomed.

03:30.796 --> 03:32.557
[coins clinking]

03:32.626 --> 03:35.456
I will see that
you're taken care of.

03:40.323 --> 03:42.946
I will find your son.

03:43.015 --> 03:45.432
That is a promise.

03:45.501 --> 03:46.950
Now cover him

03:47.019 --> 03:50.747
so that he may pass
into the kingdom of heaven

03:50.816 --> 03:54.234
and be forgiven
in the eyes of our maker.

04:04.416 --> 04:06.591
♪ ♪

04:14.288 --> 04:15.876
[quiet whistle]

04:38.657 --> 04:40.763
Forgive me, Father.

04:40.832 --> 04:43.248
It calls to me,

04:43.317 --> 04:46.838
even in contemplation
of Your words.

04:50.324 --> 04:53.016
The smell of Your crust.

04:53.085 --> 04:55.847
The way it sits in my belly.

04:57.331 --> 04:59.506
Look away.

05:06.340 --> 05:08.515
[clattering]

05:19.042 --> 05:20.458
Please.

05:20.527 --> 05:22.839
Have mercy.

05:25.704 --> 05:27.119
[splash]

05:54.768 --> 05:58.496
-[bell tolling]
-To know the Creator,

05:58.565 --> 06:02.292
one must first know
the whole of the world.

06:02.362 --> 06:06.366
And to know the whole of
the world, one must first know

06:06.435 --> 06:09.127
the Law of Two,

06:09.196 --> 06:11.301
which governs everything.

06:11.371 --> 06:15.029
Nothing is single here,
everything is double.

06:15.098 --> 06:17.929
Every element
contains its opposite.

06:17.998 --> 06:21.311
Each sunrise starts at sunset
the night before.

06:21.381 --> 06:25.177
Every man emerges from a woman.

06:25.246 --> 06:29.078
Wars are plotted at peace.

06:29.147 --> 06:31.908
Sides of the same coin.

06:31.977 --> 06:34.324
Good. Now...

06:34.394 --> 06:37.914
-come and choose your sweets.
-[kids whooping]

06:40.192 --> 06:42.022
Gather in the chapel, children.

06:42.091 --> 06:43.920
Quickly.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.165
What are you doing?

06:48.200 --> 06:50.202
I was illuminating them, Mother.

06:50.271 --> 06:51.583
Illuminating?

06:51.652 --> 06:54.034
I will have them
double their prayers.

06:54.103 --> 06:55.760
Ah, yes.

06:55.829 --> 06:59.419
I'm sure they will find all
the great answers to the world

06:59.488 --> 07:01.697
while on their knees, praying.

07:01.766 --> 07:03.837
It is your solution
to everything.

07:03.906 --> 07:06.046
You would do well to take them
out beyond the walls

07:06.115 --> 07:08.566
and show them
the claws of beasts.

07:08.635 --> 07:10.464
State your business.

07:10.533 --> 07:13.018
I have come for my bride.

07:14.813 --> 07:17.644
Ah, you disagree with the union.

07:18.679 --> 07:21.061
Speak your mind.
Let the poison out.

07:21.130 --> 07:24.202
You don't share a God,

07:24.271 --> 07:26.480
yet you hope to share a bed,

07:26.549 --> 07:29.552
and put children into the world.

07:29.621 --> 07:32.555
We share the same God,
just different sides.

07:32.624 --> 07:36.697
But I think those differences
will make the marriage bed

07:36.766 --> 07:38.699
more interesting,
don't you think?

08:12.940 --> 08:15.633
You chose well, Delphine.

08:15.702 --> 08:18.670
Pierre is a fine trapper.

08:18.739 --> 08:20.741
You chose correctly as well,
Isabelle.

08:20.810 --> 08:22.950
It all happened so fast.

08:23.019 --> 08:25.470
He was the first to look at me.

08:25.539 --> 08:29.578
That means he was drawn to you.

08:31.890 --> 08:34.686
But then he...
he barely spoke to me.

08:37.240 --> 08:38.656
It will come, in time.

08:38.725 --> 08:40.278
MELISSANDE:
Or it won't.

08:40.347 --> 08:42.694
There is no way to know
for certain.

08:44.765 --> 08:46.836
The men put on a show,
as did we.

08:46.905 --> 08:48.631
We all played our part.

08:48.700 --> 08:50.391
Some more than others.

08:50.460 --> 08:52.566
I am sure all of our men
will be kind.

08:52.635 --> 08:55.362
I just pray that he is patient.

08:55.431 --> 08:57.329
[scoffs]
Patient?

08:57.398 --> 08:59.918
No man is patient, Delphine.

08:59.987 --> 09:02.714
Not even the priests.

09:02.783 --> 09:05.545
The least he could do
is provide you with a real ring.

09:06.718 --> 09:08.202
That is what a kind man
would do.

09:08.271 --> 09:10.515
-He promised me a proper one.
-Hold him to that.

09:10.584 --> 09:14.036
He must value you more than
a strip of leather,

09:14.105 --> 09:17.177
or that is all you will ever be.

09:18.592 --> 09:21.008
SABRINE:
Mes chéries,hasten.

09:21.077 --> 09:24.287
You have an hour
before the signing.

09:24.356 --> 09:26.704
Use it to pray for guidance

09:26.773 --> 09:28.947
and protection.

09:29.016 --> 09:32.364
May you find utility and grace

09:32.433 --> 09:35.091
-and...
-Happiness?

09:36.230 --> 09:40.303
Yes, of course.
Happiness.

09:40.372 --> 09:42.582
Melissande.

09:42.651 --> 09:44.653
Come with me.

09:52.764 --> 09:54.179
Yes, Mother.

09:54.248 --> 09:57.942
I wish to talk to you
about Monsieur Trepagny.

09:58.011 --> 09:58.977
Mm.

09:59.046 --> 10:01.186
He is not like the other men.

10:01.255 --> 10:03.154
Yes.
He is rich

10:03.223 --> 10:05.190
and well-dressed.

10:05.259 --> 10:07.952
The other men smelled
of dead animals and shit.

10:08.021 --> 10:10.748
Do not be taken in
by his boasts.

10:10.817 --> 10:12.853
It is one thing
to say that you have land

10:12.922 --> 10:14.510
as far as the eye can see.

10:14.579 --> 10:17.651
It is quite another thing
to be able to hold on to it.

10:17.720 --> 10:20.343
I will see it for myself.

10:20.412 --> 10:22.552
I am sure he is the man for me.

10:22.622 --> 10:24.831
I have made my choice.

10:27.247 --> 10:28.973
I wish you luck.

10:32.908 --> 10:34.634
And our secret?

10:34.703 --> 10:37.257
A man of Monsieur Trepagny's
standing must never know

10:37.326 --> 10:38.638
I am not as God made me.

10:38.707 --> 10:41.399
It is yours to tell, child.

10:41.468 --> 10:43.643
Do you have what I gave you?

10:55.378 --> 10:57.657
JEROME:
Father Gabriel often came here

10:57.726 --> 11:00.245
to contemplate after his chores.

11:00.314 --> 11:02.800
He didn't return
for morning prayer.

11:06.182 --> 11:08.598
Perhaps he shucked his robes
and ran off.

11:08.668 --> 11:11.878
No.
He has been taken by Iroquois.

11:12.741 --> 11:14.294
And how is it you know this?

11:14.363 --> 11:15.744
The bodies are gone.

11:18.056 --> 11:21.301
Well, perhaps Father Gabriel
ate them and then

11:21.370 --> 11:23.613
-sank into the river.
-It was a sin

11:23.683 --> 11:25.857
to display the dead like that.

11:25.926 --> 11:27.617
And it is a sin
to let these savages

11:27.687 --> 11:29.343
think they can move on us.

11:31.932 --> 11:35.453
The Iroquois will return.
I have been among them.

11:35.522 --> 11:38.352
I know how their minds work.

11:38.421 --> 11:40.872
-BOUCHARD: I'll post a lookout.
-JEROME: And I'll need men

11:40.941 --> 11:43.426
to lead a search party
for Father Gabriel.

11:43.495 --> 11:45.083
I have no spare men.

11:45.152 --> 11:47.327
Intendant De Fer is coming.

11:48.742 --> 11:50.917
GUY:
Father.

12:08.520 --> 12:10.522
♪ ♪

12:29.610 --> 12:31.785
[rooster crows]

12:45.385 --> 12:47.732
I like them in a pot
with wine and herbs.

12:47.801 --> 12:50.424
Oh. You do, now?

12:50.493 --> 12:53.600
I come in a friendly
and helpful manner.

12:53.669 --> 12:55.153
A man of many talents

12:55.222 --> 12:57.431
who could be of use to you
in your current state.

12:57.500 --> 13:00.538
I know what you are after,
Monsieur Gasquet.

13:00.607 --> 13:03.852
I could tell you the all of it
if you invited me for a meal.

13:04.680 --> 13:05.888
You are welcome

13:05.957 --> 13:08.684
to pay for a meal

13:08.753 --> 13:10.548
like everybody else.

13:10.617 --> 13:12.067
As I am learning,

13:12.136 --> 13:15.553
my late husband extended credit
to the entire town.

13:16.830 --> 13:19.074
I didn't mean that sort of meal.

13:21.697 --> 13:23.078
Go away.

13:26.564 --> 13:28.014
Perhaps tomorrow, then.

13:44.962 --> 13:47.136
[grunting]

14:08.088 --> 14:10.608
You can come out now.

14:13.714 --> 14:15.233
Rabbits.

14:16.096 --> 14:18.443
Monsieur Gasquet brought them.

14:18.512 --> 14:20.618
Can you say "rabbit"?

14:20.687 --> 14:23.034
Hmm?

14:24.622 --> 14:26.900
He has designs on the inn

14:26.969 --> 14:28.937
and some other things as well.

14:30.662 --> 14:33.700
Monsieur Gasquet
does not take no for an answer.

14:33.769 --> 14:37.186
The more I push him away,
the more he sees the challenge.

14:46.023 --> 14:48.888
He has grabbed me
more than a few times,

14:48.957 --> 14:50.993
and with Francis right there.

14:51.062 --> 14:53.340
Ah, but did Francis protect me?

14:53.409 --> 14:56.067
[clicks tongue]
No.

14:56.136 --> 14:57.966
And when I demanded that he put
Monsieur Gasquet out,

14:58.035 --> 14:59.657
what did he do?

14:59.726 --> 15:01.176
Hmm?

15:01.245 --> 15:03.212
He did nothing, Renardette.

15:03.281 --> 15:05.007
Nothing.

15:06.146 --> 15:09.391
He was as useless
as a spring flower.

15:09.460 --> 15:13.084
And now I have found he has let
half the town dine on credit,

15:13.153 --> 15:14.948
and it is up to me
to collect the debt

15:15.017 --> 15:17.675
so that I may carry forth.

15:17.744 --> 15:19.263
But we will make do.

15:19.332 --> 15:20.609
Hmm?

15:20.678 --> 15:23.336
Us girls will make do,

15:23.405 --> 15:25.234
and then...

15:25.303 --> 15:27.616
we will prosper, Renardette.

15:28.720 --> 15:31.654
Oh, careful.
You will hurt yourself.

15:34.140 --> 15:36.004
-[door opens]
-[bell rings]

15:36.073 --> 15:37.626
[whispers]:
Go.

15:38.592 --> 15:40.594
[door closes]

15:46.428 --> 15:49.534
Bonjour, Mathilde.
[chuckles]

15:49.603 --> 15:50.915
Captain.

15:50.984 --> 15:53.504
I have said all I will say
on my husband's death.

15:53.573 --> 15:56.265
Oh, no,
I have not come about that.

15:57.784 --> 16:01.063
I was hoping to have a word with
the Hudson Bay man, Mr. Goames.

16:01.132 --> 16:02.858
Departed this morning.

16:02.927 --> 16:03.928
Ah.

16:03.997 --> 16:05.447
Did he say where he was off to?

16:05.516 --> 16:08.968
There was some discussion
of a trip to Quebec City.

16:10.279 --> 16:13.075
I believe they intend to return.

16:13.144 --> 16:14.697
They asked me
to keep a room for them.

16:14.766 --> 16:16.251
Better they do not return.

16:16.320 --> 16:17.700
Oh, they will be back.

16:17.769 --> 16:19.357
I'm sure of it.

16:19.426 --> 16:21.463
They are keen on finding
their missing man, Mr. Cross.

16:21.532 --> 16:24.707
That one is dead,
more than likely.

16:25.743 --> 16:27.676
Is there something else?

16:27.745 --> 16:29.022
Mm.

16:29.091 --> 16:30.679
Um...

16:30.748 --> 16:32.370
Keep a sharp eye out

16:32.439 --> 16:34.752
and don't go beyond the walls.
[chuckles softly]

16:34.821 --> 16:37.168
Especially after dark.

16:37.237 --> 16:40.102
The Iroquois paid a visit
to the docks last night.

16:40.171 --> 16:41.690
The bodies are gone.

16:41.759 --> 16:43.554
A priest missing.

16:45.901 --> 16:49.008
Have you talked to Mr. Cooke
about the troubles?

16:50.285 --> 16:52.770
What would Mr. Cooke know
of the massacre?

16:52.839 --> 16:54.634
Scheming with Gus Lafarge

16:54.703 --> 16:56.843
about the land by the creek,
they were.

16:56.912 --> 16:58.327
Henri Marth, too.

16:58.396 --> 17:00.640
-Marth?
-Oh, yeah. I heard them

17:00.709 --> 17:03.298
discuss it more than
a few times.

17:04.161 --> 17:05.541
Was this before or after

17:05.610 --> 17:07.095
you fell into dispute
with Lafarge

17:07.164 --> 17:09.062
on the matter of tables?

17:09.131 --> 17:11.271
-Eh? A fierce wobble?
-I believe

17:11.340 --> 17:13.825
he was too busy
scheming with Mr. Cooke

17:13.894 --> 17:16.483
instead of building a proper
table to sit without a wobble.

17:16.552 --> 17:18.934
Cooke and Lafarge
are responsible

17:19.003 --> 17:21.316
for the creek massacre--
is that what you are saying?

17:21.385 --> 17:25.078
I am saying I heard them
discussing it, and then,

17:25.147 --> 17:28.495
not a week later, those
poor settlers met their end.

17:30.842 --> 17:33.535
I suppose one could
see it that way.

17:33.604 --> 17:35.399
Aye.

17:35.468 --> 17:39.023
All of my head spins with rumor.

17:39.092 --> 17:41.681
What I need are facts.

17:41.750 --> 17:44.097
Of course you do.

17:45.443 --> 17:47.100
I am just an innkeep.

17:47.169 --> 17:49.206
What do I know of facts?

17:49.275 --> 17:52.554
-You are more than that,
Mathilde.
-Mm.

17:53.969 --> 17:56.040
And you are the captain

17:56.109 --> 17:58.422
sent to watch over Wobik,
not me.

17:58.491 --> 18:00.182
Yes.

18:00.251 --> 18:01.701
Yes, I am.

18:02.943 --> 18:06.499
And I will come up
with a plan, rest assured.

18:12.056 --> 18:13.816
A wise man

18:13.885 --> 18:16.233
would run Mr. Cooke
out of Wobik.

18:16.302 --> 18:18.476
Put things to order

18:18.545 --> 18:21.203
before it is hung on your head.

18:23.861 --> 18:25.345
Mm.

18:36.770 --> 18:38.151
[splashing]

18:38.220 --> 18:40.671
[grunting]

18:42.328 --> 18:45.124
Help... help me.

18:46.125 --> 18:47.298
[groans]
Mercy.

18:47.367 --> 18:48.713
I'm burned.

18:48.782 --> 18:49.990
You must leave the water.

18:50.059 --> 18:52.510
[groaning]

18:56.928 --> 19:00.104
Something for the pain, please.

19:00.173 --> 19:01.933
Wait for me.

19:02.002 --> 19:03.659
I will be back.

19:31.377 --> 19:33.586
♪ ♪

19:38.729 --> 19:40.558
[whooping]

19:56.885 --> 19:58.852
♪ ♪

20:11.831 --> 20:14.627
[both grunting]

20:33.887 --> 20:35.889
[indistinct chatter]

21:01.984 --> 21:03.676
[Hamish clears throat]

21:07.921 --> 21:09.268
Sit.

21:22.211 --> 21:25.042
Randall Cross.
Yes?

21:27.251 --> 21:28.632
Who ordered this?

21:28.701 --> 21:32.049
There was no order.
I took it upon myself.

21:32.118 --> 21:34.879
-My sister Alice...
-I still don't understand

21:34.948 --> 21:37.986
the impetus to use
company resources

21:38.055 --> 21:40.678
for a personal mission.

21:42.646 --> 21:45.476
A Mr. Elisha Cooke in Wobik

21:45.545 --> 21:47.306
says that he and Randall Cross
had a plan

21:47.375 --> 21:50.067
to stir the Iroquois
against some French settlers.

21:50.136 --> 21:51.620
Aye, that is correct.

21:51.689 --> 21:53.208
Along with the delivery
we're supposed to make.

21:53.277 --> 21:55.037
Mr. Cooke is well acquainted
with English interests

21:55.106 --> 21:56.660
in the region.

21:56.729 --> 21:59.387
Interests that include moving
forward against Wobik.

21:59.456 --> 22:02.010
Were the settlers cleared?

22:02.079 --> 22:04.150
YVON:
They were.

22:04.219 --> 22:05.772
Massacre.

22:08.706 --> 22:11.019
I want to know
if that was Cross' orders.

22:11.088 --> 22:14.194
To work with Mr. Cooke.

22:14.263 --> 22:17.266
We find allies where needed.

22:17.336 --> 22:20.062
Trade.
That is our business.

22:20.131 --> 22:22.410
-Or have you forgotten that?
-I know Randall,

22:22.479 --> 22:24.377
and such an action--

22:24.446 --> 22:26.966
a massacre of innocent people--

22:27.035 --> 22:28.623
that is not his blood.

22:30.038 --> 22:32.868
I need to know
if he was acting on orders.

22:32.937 --> 22:36.527
The orders were to make way
inland, weaken the French hold.

22:36.596 --> 22:38.771
The particulars
are not important.

22:38.840 --> 22:41.739
We have larger plans.
That is no secret.

22:42.775 --> 22:46.054
I'll ask again.
Have you made a report?

22:46.123 --> 22:48.056
Yes.

22:48.125 --> 22:49.782
I will see it, then.

23:02.864 --> 23:04.521
Furthermore, I'm granting you
and Mr. Kirkpatrick

23:04.590 --> 23:06.695
the oversee of the Wobik post

23:06.764 --> 23:08.663
and all the land
west of the creek.

23:08.732 --> 23:10.354
If Mr. Cross is to be found,

23:10.423 --> 23:11.976
the posting can be
restored to him.

23:12.045 --> 23:13.840
And if he is lost?

23:13.909 --> 23:16.429
Then you will contact
the Iroquois and let them know

23:16.498 --> 23:18.914
that should they choose
to avail themselves of muskets

23:18.983 --> 23:20.709
to rise up against the French,

23:20.778 --> 23:22.331
that they will be supplied
in abundance

23:22.401 --> 23:25.058
by their stalwart friends
at the Hudson Bay Company.

23:25.127 --> 23:28.303
-And you expect us to work
with this Mr. Cooke?
-If possible.

23:28.372 --> 23:30.719
But Mr. Cooke is not our only
asset in the region.

23:30.788 --> 23:32.169
Bill Selby is about.

23:33.895 --> 23:35.862
Now you have your assignment.

23:35.931 --> 23:37.761
Now be gone.

23:47.011 --> 23:49.600
[bell tolling]

23:49.669 --> 23:51.499
SABRINE:
Mademoiselle Isabelle Caron

23:51.568 --> 23:53.224
and Monsieur Vincent Belonger.

23:55.364 --> 23:58.022
BOUCHARD:
Hand over the notarized
property list.

24:01.578 --> 24:04.235
Félicitations.

24:07.031 --> 24:10.621
Mademoiselle Delphine Langois
and Monsieur Pierre Gasquet.

24:11.829 --> 24:14.694
BOUCHARD:
Your property list, Gasquet.

24:23.185 --> 24:26.188
SABRINE:
Mademoiselle Melissande
de Saint Rémy

24:26.257 --> 24:28.225
and Monsieur Claude Trepagny.

24:33.161 --> 24:36.682
Now I have
the whole of the moon.

24:38.407 --> 24:41.825
Please accept
my humble tithe, Mother.

24:49.626 --> 24:51.800
[indistinct chatter]

25:04.606 --> 25:06.574
I wish you happiness
and fortune.

25:06.643 --> 25:08.921
[scoffs]

25:08.990 --> 25:11.820
We are the mothers
of New France.

25:12.683 --> 25:14.823
Will we see each other again?

25:14.892 --> 25:17.481
Of course.
There will be market days.

25:17.550 --> 25:19.794
There will be time to visit.

25:19.863 --> 25:22.451
-Delphine! [laughs]
-Oh! Put me down!

25:22.521 --> 25:23.763
[Delphine gasps]

25:23.832 --> 25:25.489
My apologies.

25:25.558 --> 25:26.870
TREPAGNY:
Melissande?

25:26.939 --> 25:29.148
Step away from
this noble voyageur

25:29.217 --> 25:31.668
before he carries you off
into the woods.

25:31.737 --> 25:33.842
One pelt per man, Pierre.

25:33.911 --> 25:35.637
One pelt.

25:37.501 --> 25:39.227
Should move on.

25:43.196 --> 25:44.681
My bags.

25:44.750 --> 25:46.303
Oh, do not concern yourself.

25:46.372 --> 25:49.064
We will send for it later.

25:49.133 --> 25:51.480
My man, Rene Sel,

25:51.550 --> 25:53.586
will fetch it.

25:55.312 --> 25:57.245
Bonjour, Mathilde.

25:57.314 --> 25:58.487
Monsieur Trepagny.

25:58.557 --> 26:00.282
Are you coming to pay your bill?

26:00.351 --> 26:01.974
-[speaks French]
-Your bill.

26:02.043 --> 26:03.700
Are you coming
to settle your bill?

26:04.563 --> 26:06.634
I believe I am current.

26:06.703 --> 26:09.119
I have a balanced account
in all things.

26:09.188 --> 26:11.949
Oh, no, no. I am going
through my late husband's books,

26:12.018 --> 26:14.331
and it seems there are
a few outstanding charges.

26:14.400 --> 26:17.334
It would be a shame
if your new bride

26:17.403 --> 26:19.923
could not come to the inn
should the need arise.

26:19.992 --> 26:22.028
The need may not arise.
We are going to my Doma,

26:22.097 --> 26:23.616
and she is not yet my bride.

26:23.685 --> 26:25.376
In the eyes of the king,
yes, but

26:25.445 --> 26:28.448
there are higher bindings yet
to be done-- a proper wedding.

26:28.517 --> 26:32.383
A celebration and one to which
you will surely be invited.

26:32.452 --> 26:34.834
Now have we settled our debt?

26:36.560 --> 26:39.080
Madam.

26:46.018 --> 26:47.847
Good fortune to you.

26:53.163 --> 26:54.889
You will put a show of it on

26:54.958 --> 26:57.788
and tell Lafarge's widow her boy
took a boat to Quebec City,

26:57.857 --> 26:59.618
distraught
at his father's demise.

26:59.687 --> 27:01.412
Is it not better
if she hears it from you?

27:01.481 --> 27:03.242
No, it is not better.

27:03.311 --> 27:05.693
You will find the truth in it,
she will gladly accept it.

27:05.762 --> 27:07.039
That is your task.

27:07.108 --> 27:08.765
I understand,
but when will I be paid?

27:08.834 --> 27:10.698
The job is not finished.

27:10.767 --> 27:12.907
Until it is, you should view me
as a blunt blade

27:12.976 --> 27:14.702
that will smash you
if you cross me.

27:16.393 --> 27:17.739
You asked I take care

27:17.808 --> 27:19.534
of Lafarge's boy.
It was taken care of.

27:19.603 --> 27:21.467
That's worth something.

27:21.536 --> 27:23.952
It is.

27:25.091 --> 27:26.783
Well, this won't cover passage.

27:26.852 --> 27:29.924
A smart man
forgoes small reward now

27:29.993 --> 27:31.546
for great reward later.

27:31.615 --> 27:35.136
Compounded with work,
dedication and loyalty.

27:35.205 --> 27:36.724
Loyalty?

27:36.793 --> 27:40.106
I will teach you
the barrel game.

27:41.729 --> 27:43.178
What do you think that is--

27:43.247 --> 27:45.629
-the barrel game?
-You take timber,

27:45.698 --> 27:48.977
cut staves, make barrels,
sell them.

27:49.046 --> 27:51.290
But you think
too small, Charles.

27:51.359 --> 27:53.119
It is not
the barrels themselves.

27:53.188 --> 27:55.812
It pays to have a hand in what
goes in and out of them as well.

27:55.881 --> 27:59.263
Spice, cloth.
That brick, there.

27:59.332 --> 28:00.955
I brought that
across the Atlantic,

28:01.024 --> 28:03.129
bought the barrels
back at a discount,

28:03.198 --> 28:05.131
and here are the barrels
filled with salt fish.

28:05.200 --> 28:07.133
Up the river, I take a piece.

28:07.202 --> 28:09.342
Down the river, I take a piece.

28:09.411 --> 28:12.967
Everything for a price.

28:13.036 --> 28:14.969
Was that Gus' role
in your company?

28:15.038 --> 28:17.765
Oh, Gus' role is no more.

28:17.834 --> 28:19.939
You see, it's not
about the timber

28:20.008 --> 28:21.907
or the staves
or the hewing or joining.

28:21.976 --> 28:24.323
It's not about the making.

28:24.392 --> 28:26.428
Look at these Frenchmen.

28:26.497 --> 28:28.154
Look at them slaving away.

28:28.223 --> 28:31.192
Making their tannin,
their tar, their rope.

28:31.261 --> 28:32.641
While they are busy making,

28:32.711 --> 28:35.714
I am busy trading.

28:37.508 --> 28:39.269
With the English?

28:39.338 --> 28:42.513
It is unlawful
to trade with the English.

28:46.828 --> 28:48.934
Few staves, some wax,
it would be good as new.

28:49.003 --> 28:51.177
TREPAGNY:
If it isn't the rat.

28:54.215 --> 28:56.010
-Sir.
-I see you have found

28:56.079 --> 28:58.495
a proper Paraclete

28:58.564 --> 29:01.153
to serve your foul designs.

29:01.222 --> 29:04.328
I told your friend Sel
the rat will find a hole.

29:04.397 --> 29:07.607
You may take him, if you like,
though I do have use for him.

29:07.676 --> 29:09.333
He is yours.

29:09.402 --> 29:10.990
I forfeit my claim.

29:11.059 --> 29:13.855
Gladly and with all my heart,

29:13.924 --> 29:15.788
I release you.

29:15.857 --> 29:17.583
Good luck to you both.

29:17.652 --> 29:19.758
I am off with my new bride,

29:19.827 --> 29:21.414
full of bright thoughts.

29:21.483 --> 29:23.313
BOUCHARD:
Step aside, Trepagny.

29:23.382 --> 29:26.557
I have matters to put right
with Mr. Cooke.

29:29.043 --> 29:32.494
-What is this?
-Tell me where Henri Marth is.

29:33.392 --> 29:36.913
-I do not know.
-You are a liar.

29:38.224 --> 29:40.882
This is not a proper hearing.
You have no right.

29:40.951 --> 29:43.851
Your rights in New France
died with your wife.

29:43.920 --> 29:46.888
I hereby exercise
the power of the crown,

29:46.957 --> 29:48.752
and I offer you a choice.

29:48.821 --> 29:50.340
I relieve you of your house,

29:50.409 --> 29:53.515
your cooperage,
and cast you out of New France.

29:53.584 --> 29:56.967
Or you submit now to the fiddle.

29:57.899 --> 29:59.659
I will not be scapegoated.

29:59.728 --> 30:02.973
Then confess your hand
in the murder of the innkeep.

30:03.042 --> 30:05.113
COOKE:
That was Gus' business,
not mine.

30:05.182 --> 30:07.978
Then there is the business
of the bloody massacre.

30:08.047 --> 30:10.360
I hear there were more
than Iroquois at play.

30:10.429 --> 30:14.295
Eh? A fine and poisonous
English mind, in fact.

30:14.364 --> 30:18.333
Where is your evidence,
you drunk?

30:18.402 --> 30:21.233
Mr. Cooke, this will
go better for you

30:21.302 --> 30:23.442
if you do not
play me for a fool.

30:28.378 --> 30:31.105
The fiddle will help us
find the truth.

30:32.900 --> 30:35.212
-Eh...
-All right!

30:35.281 --> 30:38.975
All right!
I submit.

30:47.224 --> 30:50.296
There is a lock of hair
in my pocket.

30:50.365 --> 30:53.127
Take it out, give it to me.

30:56.647 --> 30:57.959
It belonged to my wife.

30:58.028 --> 31:01.618
Give it to me, Bouchard.

31:01.687 --> 31:03.240
[laughs]

31:06.002 --> 31:08.176
WOMAN:
Dirty English!

31:09.488 --> 31:13.388
You will stand bared
before the people of Wobik

31:13.457 --> 31:16.081
for the murder
of Francis Geffard!

31:16.150 --> 31:18.980
[shouting, jeering]

31:20.775 --> 31:22.915
Let Mr. Cooke's punishment

31:22.984 --> 31:26.194
be an example to every man
in Wobik!

31:26.263 --> 31:28.610
MAN:
Throw away the key!

31:45.869 --> 31:48.044
♪ ♪

32:12.033 --> 32:13.483
[inhaling sharply]

32:13.552 --> 32:16.382
[groans]

32:16.451 --> 32:17.763
[grunts]

32:17.832 --> 32:19.696
You're Wyandot?

32:25.840 --> 32:28.360
Have you told anyone of me?

32:30.362 --> 32:31.535
No.

32:35.229 --> 32:37.300
Do I have your word
that if you heal,

32:37.369 --> 32:40.579
you will leave this land
and not come back?

32:40.648 --> 32:42.339
I c...

32:42.408 --> 32:44.514
Yeah.

32:44.583 --> 32:46.757
Good.

32:49.001 --> 32:50.934
Now sleep.

32:51.003 --> 32:53.488
I will return with food.

32:55.835 --> 32:57.389
If the pain is too much,

32:57.458 --> 33:00.909
take all of this in one swallow.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.601
Spotted hemlock.

33:02.670 --> 33:06.156
You will go to sleep
and not wake up.

33:16.580 --> 33:18.444
My mother was a wit,
and I-I know that I said

33:18.513 --> 33:21.171
my favorite of her sayings was
the one about the bloated monk

33:21.240 --> 33:23.035
who feared his vow of silence
covered farts,

33:23.104 --> 33:25.244
but I don't have
her way with the phrase.

33:25.313 --> 33:27.143
I'm afraid I'll word it wrong.

33:27.212 --> 33:29.214
Tell it another time, chéri.

33:29.283 --> 33:31.802
The woods reward silence.

33:31.871 --> 33:35.392
It is in the silence we hear
things not of this world.

33:37.222 --> 33:40.259
Come.
I will show you.

33:45.506 --> 33:47.818
You must step very carefully.

33:49.613 --> 33:52.133
Here and here.

34:08.805 --> 34:10.772
Are you nervous
of what you will find

34:10.841 --> 34:12.843
when you reach my Doma?

34:14.949 --> 34:16.364
Perhaps.

34:20.437 --> 34:22.232
[grunts]

34:22.301 --> 34:25.925
Which means
you know surprises loom.

34:25.994 --> 34:27.410
[gasps]

34:27.479 --> 34:29.722
TREPAGNY:
Ah. [chuckles]

34:34.693 --> 34:36.177
It's fine.

34:41.286 --> 34:44.047
They are everywhere on my Doma

34:44.116 --> 34:45.807
this time of year.

34:47.326 --> 34:50.295
And there are the mice,
of course.

34:50.364 --> 34:53.539
And many hawks,
which also eat the mice,

34:53.608 --> 34:55.127
but prefer to eat the snakes

34:55.196 --> 34:58.199
and sometimes get both.

35:00.098 --> 35:02.686
There is also another creature

35:02.755 --> 35:05.033
that menaces them all.

35:05.103 --> 35:08.727
The child
of my housekeeper Mari.

35:08.796 --> 35:12.040
This is one of the surprises
I will warn you of now.

35:12.110 --> 35:13.870
You have a housekeeper?

35:13.939 --> 35:16.907
I depend on her.
She is a Wyandot woman.

35:16.976 --> 35:19.738
She may test you,
she may throw curses at you.

35:19.807 --> 35:23.949
Then you must put her
in her place.

35:24.018 --> 35:27.780
She has long since
forgotten her place, I'm afraid.

35:27.849 --> 35:30.473
Come. I will tell you
the story of the wasp

35:30.542 --> 35:33.441
that followed me for two days.

35:35.754 --> 35:38.343
Yes.
I looked and saw...

35:52.840 --> 35:54.359
[exhales]

36:16.933 --> 36:18.831
♪ ♪

36:39.783 --> 36:42.234
Come out of there.

36:44.202 --> 36:45.548
[coins clicking]

36:47.377 --> 36:50.863
Stayed where I put you.

36:50.932 --> 36:52.417
Are you going to kill me?

36:52.486 --> 36:53.832
Not if you leave.

36:54.902 --> 36:56.386
Do you understand?

36:56.455 --> 36:58.354
Follow the river to Quebec.

36:58.423 --> 37:01.184
Please.
I want to go home.

37:01.253 --> 37:03.876
And I should do
as I was paid to do.

37:03.945 --> 37:06.327
Smash your brains out.

37:06.396 --> 37:09.882
Now go.
I'm giving you a chance.

37:11.884 --> 37:15.233
-Tell my mother I love her.
-I shall tell her you're dead.

37:15.302 --> 37:16.820
Now go.

37:30.006 --> 37:31.801
Do you like it here?

37:33.389 --> 37:35.529
It's perfect.

37:35.598 --> 37:37.358
We shall have more.

37:37.427 --> 37:40.016
More land.

37:40.085 --> 37:41.051
More family.

37:41.120 --> 37:43.847
Of course, a proper house.

37:53.719 --> 37:55.411
Come.

38:09.045 --> 38:10.322
Put it on.

38:16.949 --> 38:18.296
Please.

38:36.969 --> 38:39.420
Everything is good?

38:39.489 --> 38:42.043
Ah, come on.
[laughs]

38:43.976 --> 38:47.221
It's good? Perfect.
Good, you liked it?

38:47.290 --> 38:49.361
Uh, bouger, bouger, bouger.

38:49.430 --> 38:51.639
Bouger, bouger.

38:51.708 --> 38:53.883
Okay, I'll be right back.

39:06.344 --> 39:07.759
What are you doing?

39:07.828 --> 39:10.002
I've been waiting
for a meal, Mathilde.

39:15.594 --> 39:16.975
You have been in the drink.

39:17.044 --> 39:18.597
[chuckles]
True.

39:18.666 --> 39:19.978
Monsieur Gasquet,

39:20.047 --> 39:22.221
if you will leave
my kitchen at once,

39:22.290 --> 39:24.845
-I shall prepare your food.
-And I shall be direct
with you, Mathilde.

39:24.914 --> 39:27.468
I am not asking for that.
I am asking you

39:27.537 --> 39:28.952
to let me get back to my work.

39:29.021 --> 39:31.299
[chuckles]
I would partner with you.

39:31.369 --> 39:34.579
There is no more need
for you to put up resistance.

39:34.648 --> 39:37.375
You will need a man.

39:37.444 --> 39:39.066
-Better you see that now.
-No!

39:40.550 --> 39:43.519
[grunts]
No!

39:43.588 --> 39:45.624
Monsieur Gasquet,

39:45.693 --> 39:49.490
I am telling you
I do not need a man.

39:49.559 --> 39:51.872
Now, if you will please
leave my kitchen.

39:51.941 --> 39:53.529
At once.

39:53.598 --> 39:56.117
I am sorry, Mathilde.

40:16.793 --> 40:19.140
Shh. It's okay.
Don't.

40:19.209 --> 40:21.004
Shh.

40:47.790 --> 40:49.964
[crickets chirping outside]

41:10.364 --> 41:12.193
I'm cold.

41:14.230 --> 41:15.818
Come over here.

41:15.887 --> 41:17.820
I will warm you up.

41:31.696 --> 41:34.699
Take off the dress.

41:35.562 --> 41:38.668
You are my wife now.

41:38.737 --> 41:40.843
Take it off.

41:59.724 --> 42:02.209
Come to me.

42:07.904 --> 42:10.873
[quietly]:
Pierre, I'm sorry.

42:24.438 --> 42:26.923
It's been a tiring day.

42:28.304 --> 42:30.030
I'm going to sleep.

42:32.480 --> 42:34.655
You should do the same.

42:58.472 --> 43:00.129
[door closes]

43:24.325 --> 43:26.673
Is something wrong?

43:29.227 --> 43:31.850
Is this it?

43:31.919 --> 43:34.577
TREPAGNY:
It is veiled

43:34.646 --> 43:36.234
in the dark.

43:36.303 --> 43:40.410
The daylight will open your eyes
to its beauty.

43:56.012 --> 43:58.187
I wish to see it all.

43:58.256 --> 44:01.639
You will see everything
in the morning.

44:10.544 --> 44:13.789
That is my contemplation room.

44:13.858 --> 44:16.308
I will show it to you
another time.

44:16.377 --> 44:19.449
I wish to see so that I might
better know my new husband.

44:19.518 --> 44:24.075
One must have secrets.
Don't you agree?

44:24.144 --> 44:27.388
For now, I will allow you
just this one.

44:29.425 --> 44:31.220
Shall we go?

44:31.289 --> 44:32.462
Yes.

44:41.230 --> 44:43.715
The true binding
of a man and woman

44:43.784 --> 44:45.821
must have a ceremony

44:45.890 --> 44:48.133
befitting the sanctity.

44:48.202 --> 44:49.963
A celebration.

44:50.032 --> 44:51.171
Exactement.

44:51.240 --> 44:53.898
A party to celebrate our union,

44:53.967 --> 44:57.798
so it may be bound
in the vault of heaven.

44:57.867 --> 45:00.939
But tonight...

45:01.008 --> 45:04.771
we must bind and consummate

45:04.840 --> 45:07.981
as God intended all creatures.

45:08.844 --> 45:11.467
Even the snake.

45:38.528 --> 45:40.392
♪ ♪

46:03.588 --> 46:06.073
♪ ♪

46:28.889 --> 46:31.512
[Rene panting]

46:42.178 --> 46:43.559
[grunts]

46:46.320 --> 46:48.219
[groans]

46:54.708 --> 46:57.228
[grunts]

46:59.886 --> 47:01.266
[twig snaps]

47:16.488 --> 47:17.904
Good.

47:17.973 --> 47:21.424
I see now
what kind of man you are.

47:23.771 --> 47:26.015
The lock of my wife's hair.

47:26.084 --> 47:28.466
Fetch it for me.

47:42.687 --> 47:45.069
[sighs]

47:58.289 --> 48:00.084
Would you sit with me?

48:24.902 --> 48:27.042
[crickets chirping]

48:45.094 --> 48:47.269
♪ ♪

49:04.976 --> 49:06.495
[grunts softly]

49:06.564 --> 49:08.290
[urinating]

